the house...

235
00:19:38,858 --> 00:19:42,692
because I'm so far behind
on the payments.

236
00:19:42,733 --> 00:19:45,525
And I'm going to lose Linda.

237
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:47,608
I know it.

238
00:19:48,233 --> 00:19:50,150
I know I am.

239
00:19:53,608 --> 00:19:55,817
She loves you, Bill.

240
00:20:00,817 --> 00:20:02,525
Ah, don't cry.

241
00:20:09,608 --> 00:20:11,067
I shouldn't have told you.

242
00:20:11,150 --> 00:20:14,108
- Don't worry. It's OK.
- I shouldn't have.

243
00:20:14,233 --> 00:20:16,942
No, I think you've got...
enough stuff...

244
00:20:17,025 --> 00:20:20,567
Would it make you feel better
if I told you a secret?

245
00:20:20,692 --> 00:20:22,608
What could you tell me?

246
00:20:28,983 --> 00:20:30,983
I'm going blind.

247
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:41,442
Not yet, but... soon.

248
00:20:44,525 --> 00:20:46,733
Maybe sometime this year.

249
00:20:56,108 --> 00:20:58,108
Blind?

250
00:21:02,108 --> 00:21:04,983
It's not as bad as it sounds.

251
00:21:06,692 --> 00:21:08,650
It's a...

252
00:21:09,275 --> 00:21:11,275
It's a family thing.

253
00:21:15,067 --> 00:21:18,483
- But blind?
- I've always known it.

254
00:21:18,567 --> 00:21:22,150
From... from...
I was a little girl, I knew.

255
00:21:27,442 --> 00:21:29,442
And you're OK?

256
00:21:30,442 --> 00:21:32,650
Well, I came to America,

257
00:21:32,733 --> 00:21:37,983
because in America they can give
Gene an operation, you know?

258
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:40,483
Gene?

259
00:21:40,608 --> 00:21:43,025
But, he doesn't know about it.

260
00:21:44,525 --> 00:21:48,692
You mustn't tell him
because then it could get worse.

261
00:21:48,817 --> 00:21:52,983
I just have to save up money,
you know. Enough money to...

262
00:21:54,067 --> 00:21:56,025
Oh, I almost got it.

263
00:21:56,900 --> 00:21:59,567
To, um... For the operation.

264
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:04,233
They can operate on Gene
when he turns 13.

265
00:22:04,317 --> 00:22:07,275
You made up that story
about your father?

266
00:22:09,983 --> 00:22:14,442
I never had a father.
I made up his name too.

267
00:22:16,608 --> 00:22:21,525
That's why you put in all these
hours and do everything you do.

268
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:26,067
For him? For his operation?

269
00:22:31,067 --> 00:22:34,150
Well, it is my fault... I guess.

270
00:22:35,483 --> 00:22:37,608
How is it your fault?

271
00:22:42,442 --> 00:22:47,442
Because I knew he would...
he would have bad eyes like me.

272
00:22:49,983 --> 00:22:52,775
But I had him all the same.

273
00:22:56,358 --> 00:22:58,317
You're very strong.

274
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:02,233
I'm not strong.

275
00:23:02,942 --> 00:23:06,942
I've got little games I play
when it goes really hard.

276
00:23:08,567 --> 00:23:11,275
When I'm working in the factory...

277
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:17,317
and the machines,
they make these... rhythms.

278
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:25,608
And I just start dreaming
and it all becomes music.

279
00:23:25,692 --> 00:23:28,275
- You like movies, don't you?
- I love them.

280
00:23:28,358 --> 00:23:31,608
- Yeah?
- I just love the musicals.

281
00:23:31,692 --> 00:23:35,067
- When they're all tap-dancing?
- All of them tap-dancing.

282
00:23:35,150 --> 00:23:37,733
All of them in those huge long lines.

283
00:23:37,817 --> 00:23:40,942
I... Wouldn't you like
to be in that line?

284
00:23:42,233 --> 00:23:44,067
- Yeah.
- Just kicking your feet.

285
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:45,733
Yeah.

286
00:23:45,817 --> 00:23:50,483
When they're like spiralling up
the huge enormous wedding cakes.

287
00:23:50,525 --> 00:23:52,650
- Yeah, yeah.
- To the top?

288
00:23:52,775 --> 00:23:55,733
Isn't it annoying when they
do the last song?

289
00:23:55,817 --> 00:23:57,108
Why?

290
00:23:57,192 --> 00:23:59,400
You know when it goes really big

291
00:23:59,525 --> 00:24:02,858
and the camera goes, like,
out of the roof

292
00:24:02,942 --> 00:24:05,692
and you just know it's going to end.

293
00:24:05,733 --> 00:24:08,608
I hate that. I really hate that.

294
00:24:08,692 --> 00:24:12,733
I used to cheat when I was
a little girl in Czechoslovakia.

295
00:24:12,858 --> 00:24:18,525
I would leave the cinema just
after the next to last song.

296
00:24:18,608 --> 00:24:21,567
And the film
would just go on forever.

297
00:24:24,400 --> 00:24:27,650
- It's lovely, isn't it?
- It is lovely.

298
00:24:29,150 --> 00:24:32,067
- Selma?
- Yeah?

299
00:24:32,483 --> 00:24:35,192
Thank you for telling me your secret.

300
00:24:37,025 --> 00:24:39,275
Thanks for telling me yours.

301
00:24:41,025 --> 00:24:42,733
Mum's the word, right?

302
00:24:42,775 --> 00:24:44,442
Mum?

303
00:24:45,567 --> 00:24:48,483
- We don't tell anybody.
- Oh, yes.

304
00:24:49,567 --> 00:24:51,608
I won't tell anyone.

305
00:24:51,733 --> 00:24:53,692
Good night.

306
00:25:13,608 --> 00:25:15,025
Thank you.

307
00:25:15,067 --> 00:25:17,358
So, can I get you another?

308
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:19,150
Yeah, sure.

309
00:25:19,233 --> 00:25:23,192
- How about a big one?
- How many is there in a big one?

310
00:25:23,275 --> 00:25:25,192
Ten thousand.

311
00:25:26,150 --> 00:25:27,608
I'll have a big one.

312
00:25:31,608 --> 00:25:34,358
What's this guy's name again?

313
00:25:34,775 --> 00:25:36,233
Who?

314
00:25:36,317 --> 00:25:40,275
The old man - the guy we're
carding these pins for?

315
00:25:41,775 --> 00:25:46,733
Her father? I know. Oldrich, right?

316
00:25:46,775 --> 00:25:48,192
Yeah.

317
00:25:48,233 --> 00:25:52,775
Oldrich Novy.
He used to dance in Prague.

318
00:25:52,858 --> 00:25:56,067
You commies make a big deal
out of sharing everything.

319
00:25:56,150 --> 00:25:59,775
Yeah, it's a good thing.

320
00:25:59,900 --> 00:26:01,817
What are you doing here,

321
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:05,650
if Czechoslovakia is so much
better than the US of A?

322
00:26:41,650 --> 00:26:43,858
No, Selma, no!

323
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:46,025
There are two plates.

324
00:26:48,442 --> 00:26:50,692
It's all right.

325
00:26:53,692 --> 00:26:57,608
You know what happens when you put
two plates in, don't you?

326
00:26:59,692 --> 00:27:01,650
Well, she didn't. It didn't..

327
00:27:01,733 --> 00:27:03,692
You destroy the tool!

328
00:27:05,108 --> 00:27:08,608
Takes a whole day to mend.
Never two plates, Selma!

329
00:27:08,775 --> 00:27:12,233
You cheated the doctor.
You shouldn't be working here.

330
00:27:12,317 --> 00:27:14,817
How dare you! How much can you see?

331
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:17,608
We could do it with our eyes closed.

332
00:27:17,692 --> 00:27:19,025
No.

333
00:27:19,108 --> 00:27:21,525
It's just because I was daydreaming.

334
00:27:21,608 --> 00:27:24,483
Daydreaming? Dreaming about what?

335
00:27:24,525 --> 00:27:28,150
- I just hear music.
- Come on, Selma. Music?

336
00:27:28,233 --> 00:27:32,025
You could cut off your hand.
You have to watch out.

337
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:34,358
Promise me you'll stay awake.

338
00:27:35,275 --> 00:27:37,608
I promise I will stop daydreaming.

339
00:27:37,692 --> 00:27:40,192
No, you're not really,
you repeat but...

340
00:27:40,275 --> 00:27:43,025
I don't know why I bother that much.

341
00:27:44,275 --> 00:27:46,233
Hi, Selma.

342
00:27:47,192 --> 00:27:50,525
If you're not going with Kathy
can I give you a lift?

343
00:27:50,608 --> 00:27:54,692
I don't want a boyfriend.
I- I told you.

344
00:27:56,150 --> 00:27:59,442
You're a really nice guy,
Jeff, but...

345
00:27:59,567 --> 00:28:02,567
I just don't have time
for a boyfriend.

346
00:28:02,650 --> 00:28:04,567
Not right now.

347
00:28:05,858 --> 00:28:07,900
I know.

348
00:28:07,942 --> 00:28:11,692
If I wanted a boyfriend,
it would be you, Jeff.

349
00:28:11,775 --> 00:28:14,233
I just don't want one right now.

350
00:28:20,817 --> 00:28:25,025
No problem, you know - on the
back - to have the bike there.

351
00:28:25,108 --> 00:28:26,858
Yeah.

352
00:28:32,108 --> 00:28:33,567
Bye, Jeff.

353
00:28:33,650 --> 00:28:35,858
I don't think it's very safe,

354
00:28:35,942 --> 00:28:38,942
riding the bike wearing glasses
and all.

355
00:28:39,025 --> 00:28:41,483
- Selma?
- Bye, Jeff.

356
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:51,817
Are you OK?

357
00:28:52,650 --> 00:28:54,567
Yeah, I'm fine.

358
00:28:55,358 --> 00:28:57,858
- Hi, Selma.
- Hi, Bill.

359
00:28:57,942 --> 00:29:00,650
- Heading home?
- Oh, yes.

360
00:29:00,692 --> 00:29:02,692
Wanna throw that in the back?

361
00:29:02,733 --> 00:29:04,858
That would be lovely. Yes, please.

362
00:29:04,942 --> 00:29:07,817
- Hi, Jeff.
- Hey, did you see the truck?

363
00:29:07,900 --> 00:29:09,233
No.

364
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:12,567
Like, driving like crazy.

365
00:29:13,858 --> 00:29:17,358
- He what?
- He was driving like crazy.

366
00:29:21,858 --> 00:29:23,817
Getting dirty.

367
00:29:26,817 --> 00:29:28,483
Thank you.

368
00:29:28,525 --> 00:29:32,650
- Bye, Jeff.
- Bye. Thank you, Bill.

369
00:29:35,775 --> 00:29:37,692
- OK?
- OK.

370
00:29:43,400 --> 00:29:47,442
