Just be a month.

374
00:30:00,150 --> 00:30:02,650
This money's Gene's.

375
00:30:04,900 --> 00:30:08,317
- I'm sorry, Bill.
- I shouldn't have asked.

376
00:30:08,358 --> 00:30:10,858
Don't worry,
there's no harm in asking.

377
00:30:10,900 --> 00:30:14,692
No, I shouldn't have asked.
Linda wants new couches.

378
00:30:16,275 --> 00:30:18,025
Huh.

379
00:30:21,317 --> 00:30:23,275
I could always shoot myself.

380
00:30:24,983 --> 00:30:27,567
You mustn't say things like that.

381
00:30:29,067 --> 00:30:31,692
It'd just... make things easier.

382
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:35,817
- You know that, Bill?
- No, Selma...

383
00:30:35,900 --> 00:30:39,025
- You mustn't say those things.
- I'm kidding.

384
00:30:45,525 --> 00:30:49,733
Hi, Selma. Come on in. Hi, Gene.

385
00:30:49,858 --> 00:30:52,275
- Good morning.
- Hi.

386
00:31:01,858 --> 00:31:05,817
- How are you?
- Fine, thank you.

387
00:31:10,858 --> 00:31:14,358
- Can I see the gun?
- Yeah, go on.

388
00:31:16,525 --> 00:31:20,150
- He's got a gun?
- Sure, he's a police officer.

389
00:31:20,233 --> 00:31:23,733
Just didn't know he'd keep
it here, in the house.

390
00:31:23,858 --> 00:31:27,900
Oh, yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Keeps it in his desk.

391
00:31:36,983 --> 00:31:39,025
Maybe I should pay more rent.

392
00:31:39,150 --> 00:31:42,108
It's been the same
since I've been here.

393
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:44,317
No, Selma. I won't hear it.

394
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:48,108
You keep your money,
you need it more than we do.

395
00:32:35,442 --> 00:32:37,317
Two boxes?

396
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:41,275
You are going to do two boxes
at the same time now?

397
00:32:41,317 --> 00:32:43,817
- Yeah.
- Selma, ten o'clock, then?

398
00:32:43,858 --> 00:32:45,817
Yeah, ten o'clock.

399
00:32:46,983 --> 00:32:49,067
