Do you live here?

509
00:42:02,275 --> 00:42:05,942
She might say yes to a ride
when it's this late.

510
00:42:06,067 --> 00:42:09,108
Maybe Kathy... wants a ride.

511
00:42:09,233 --> 00:42:11,400
No, it's all right.

512
00:42:12,608 --> 00:42:14,817
What's that on your hand?

513
00:42:14,900 --> 00:42:17,483
- She cut her...
- Cut my finger.

514
00:42:17,608 --> 00:42:21,275
- It's going to be all right.
- The plates are sharp.

515
00:42:21,358 --> 00:42:23,608
- Good night.
- Careful.

516
00:43:20,733 --> 00:43:23,817
I think I found a solution
to my problem.

517
00:43:25,775 --> 00:43:28,025
That makes me really happy.

518
00:43:28,108 --> 00:43:30,692
It's nothing special.

519
00:43:30,733 --> 00:43:34,608
But I've made up my mind
I'm gonna tell Linda.

520
00:43:38,900 --> 00:43:42,525
I mean, after all,
she loves me, and...

521
00:43:45,775 --> 00:43:48,942
We'll just work it out together.

522
00:43:49,025 --> 00:43:52,442
That sounds like
a really good idea, Bill.

523
00:43:59,692 --> 00:44:01,858
Sorry. I'll let you get to bed.

524
00:44:01,900 --> 00:44:05,483
I guess I'm kinda tired.
Thanks, Bill.

525
00:44:05,567 --> 00:44:08,483
- Good night, Selma.
- Good night, Bill.

526
00:44:18,525 --> 00:44:20,400
Bill?

527
00:45:40,525 --> 00:45:42,108
What's happening now?

528
00:46:04,067 --> 00:46:06,608
