00:46:48,942 --> 00:46:52,150
Kathy, what are you doing?
This is Maria's entrance.

542
00:46:52,233 --> 00:46:55,233
Yes, I'm sorry. It's my mistake.

543
00:46:55,275 --> 00:46:57,233
Please, I don't have all night.

544
00:46:57,317 --> 00:47:00,067
- Six steps.
- OK.

545
00:47:09,525 --> 00:47:10,900
Good.

546
00:47:10,983 --> 00:47:13,483
OK, I'm thinking maybe, Selma,

547
00:47:13,650 --> 00:47:17,233
you could take a little circle
around Boris on this next part.

548
00:47:17,317 --> 00:47:20,692
Unless you have something else
you want to suggest.

549
00:47:20,775 --> 00:47:22,483
I'm open.

550
00:47:23,692 --> 00:47:25,025
OK?

551
00:47:25,150 --> 00:47:27,983
- Samuel?
- Yes?

552
00:47:28,025 --> 00:47:29,900
I need to talk to you.

553
00:47:30,025 --> 00:47:33,317
If it's about the drummer,
I have been looking everywhere...

554
00:47:33,400 --> 00:47:37,108
- I promised you...
- It's not about the drummer.

555
00:47:41,317 --> 00:47:45,150
- Just a quick word.
- Do you wanna go outside?

556
00:47:45,275 --> 00:47:47,275
- Yeah.
- OK.

557
00:47:47,317 --> 00:47:51,358
# And up in the nursery
an absurd little bird

558
00:47:51,442 --> 00:47:55,025
# Is popping out to say cuckoo

559
00:47:57,067 --> 00:47:59,442
I'm... I'm not gonna play Maria.

560
00:47:59,567 --> 00:48:00,942
What?

561
00:48:02,233 --> 00:48:04,442
My heart just isn't in this,

562
00:48:04,525 --> 00:48:08,733
like, I shouldn't be wasting
my time on something...

563
00:48:08,817 --> 00:48:11,775
that isn't that important, really.

564
00:48:13,733 --> 00:48:18,317
I've been watching Suzan
and she's... she's great.

565
00:48:18,442 --> 00:48:22,567
She's... she's a much better
dancer than I am.

566
00:48:22,650 --> 00:48:25,983
Suzan's terrific,
I'm not denying that.

567
00:48:26,067 --> 00:48:29,150
But, you... I thought
you lived for musicals.

568
00:48:29,192 --> 00:48:32,275
So you've been pretending
the whole time?

569
00:48:32,358 --> 00:48:35,983
Yes, I've just been pretending.

570
00:48:36,067 --> 00:48:39,233
I don't know what else...
Everything's cast now.

571
00:48:39,275 --> 00:48:41,025
Yeah.

572
00:48:41,108 --> 00:48:44,900
The only part that's left
is the old nun.

573
00:48:44,942 --> 00:48:48,692
I don't think you'd want
that part. There's no dancing.

574
00:48:50,192 --> 00:48:52,150
She's quite serious, then?

575
00:48:52,275 --> 00:48:55,150
She's serious, yeah.
It's important for the part.

576
00:48:55,192 --> 00:48:59,275
And not dancing, really. No.

577
00:48:59,358 --> 00:49:02,025
I could put a little dancing
in there.

578
00:49:02,108 --> 00:49:04,317
You think so?

579
00:49:04,442 --> 00:49:07,233
I didn't have it in mind.

580
00:49:07,317 --> 00:49:09,650
You can have your tapping.

581
00:49:11,150 --> 00:49:15,233
She could be just a little
humorous once in a while.

582
00:49:15,317 --> 00:49:17,525
Even though she's a nun.

583
00:49:19,275 --> 00:49:22,317
You'll always be my perfect Maria.

584
00:49:24,650 --> 00:49:26,358
Where are all the hairpins today?

585
00:49:26,483 --> 00:49:28,400
I left them at home.

586
00:49:28,483 --> 00:49:31,025
And she won't be playing Maria.

587
00:49:31,067 --> 00:49:34,192
What will I do
if I can't bawl you out

588
00:49:34,275 --> 00:49:36,775
for learning your lines
on company time?

589
00:49:36,858 --> 00:49:40,067
One... two... three!

590
00:49:42,817 --> 00:49:45,400
What kind of a joke is that?

591
00:49:45,525 --> 00:49:49,067
- I need a word with you.
- We're talking now.

592
00:49:49,150 --> 00:49:51,817
All right. Come on.

593
00:50:00,317 --> 00:50:02,442
Please, sit down.

594
00:50:04,442 --> 00:50:06,858
We were off for the whole day.

595
00:50:06,942 --> 00:50:10,275
Everything stops when the
machine breaks, you know that.

596
00:50:11,858 --> 00:50:17,275
I- I can do my job just fine
if I stick to the day shift.

597
00:50:18,358 --> 00:50:20,775
This won't happen again.

598
00:50:21,858 --> 00:50:24,275
I- I daydream too much.

599
00:50:24,358 --> 00:50:26,900
I- I decided to quit.

600
00:50:30,983 --> 00:50:34,150
I guess, then, I forgot.

601
00:50:36,983 --> 00:50:39,983
I've been ordered
to let you go, Selma.

602
00:50:46,858 --> 00:50:51,692
You don't have to pay for the machine
you broke. I got them to agree.

603
00:50:51,775 --> 00:50:53,733
Thanks, Norman.

604
00:50:57,317 --> 00:50:59,442
This is your, ah... salary.

605
00:51:02,317 --> 00:51:05,150
And you know, ah...

606
00:51:05,275 --> 00:51:08,858
maybe we can find you something
away from the machines...

607
00:51:10,275 --> 00:51:12,817
where your eyesight
wouldn't matter so much.

608
00:51:12,858 --> 00:51:16,483
- Not right away.
- That's very kind.

609
00:51:16,567 --> 00:51:19,067
But, um, I'll be OK.

610
00:51:19,150 --> 00:51:21,067
I- I really will.

611
00:51:22,067 --> 00:51:24,400
- Thanks, Norman.
- Thank you, Selma.

612
00:51:24,483 --> 00:51:26,317
Thank you.

613
00:51:42,858 --> 00:51:47,817
What is she going to do now?!
Did you ever think about that?!

614
00:51:49,900 --> 00:51:53,817
Don't worry, Kathy, really.
I'm going to be fine.

615
00:51:55,442 --> 00:51:57,400
Has anybody seen Jeff today?

616
00:51:57,483 --> 00:52:01,067
He's usually here early, Selma.
But not this early.

617
00:52:01,150 --> 00:52:03,358
That's a shame.

618
00:52:11,983 --> 00:52:13,483
Selma!

619
00:52:15,942 --> 00:52:17,608
Selma.

620
00:52:20,900 --> 00:52:23,483
I could give you a lift if you want.

621
00:52:24,442 --> 00:52:27,067
I- I will need a lift... later.

622
00:52:28,775 --> 00:52:32,733
I need to do something important
at, ah... three.

623
00:52:34,317 --> 00:52:37,733
You need to get your truck,
then, don't you?

624
00:52:37,817 --> 00:52:39,775
Yeah.

625
00:52:46,567 --> 00:52:49,608
Train's coming.
Get off the track, Jeff.

626
00:52:49,692 --> 00:52:52,025
You have to be careful.

627
00:52:52,067 --> 00:52:54,067
Stick to the side.

