to go to the bank for his box.

674
00:59:29,608 --> 00:59:31,942
Is he... is he upstairs?

675
00:59:34,483 --> 00:59:37,817
I know everything, Selma.
Bill told me.

676
00:59:37,858 --> 00:59:40,317
I want you to move out.

677
00:59:44,983 --> 00:59:48,567
I don't understand. What do you know?

678
00:59:51,608 --> 00:59:53,817
That you came on to him.

679
00:59:53,942 --> 00:59:58,483
That you asked him into the trailer,
but he turned you down.

680
01:00:03,900 --> 01:00:06,650
You've got nothing
to say for yourself?!

681
01:00:07,692 --> 01:00:10,733
No. I want to talk to Bill.

682
01:00:30,483 --> 01:00:32,442
Hi, Bill.

683
01:00:35,483 --> 01:00:40,858
Linda saw me go up to the, um...
up to the trailer.

684
01:00:44,275 --> 01:00:47,567
I told her it was you
who wanted to...

685
01:00:47,650 --> 01:00:51,067
That you'd... That you'd fallen
in love with me.

686
01:00:51,192 --> 01:00:54,858
I know. She told me.

687
01:00:54,942 --> 01:00:57,150
And what did you tell her?

688
01:00:57,233 --> 01:00:59,275
Nothing.

689
01:00:59,400 --> 01:01:01,942
You didn't tell her I was lying?

690
01:01:02,067 --> 01:01:04,233
Mum's the word, right?

691
01:01:11,525 --> 01:01:14,525
Linda told me you went to the bank.

692
01:01:15,733 --> 01:01:19,025
I went to the bank
to ask for more time.

693
01:01:22,233 --> 01:01:26,650
But I couldn't do it
and I brought the box home instead.

694
01:01:26,733 --> 01:01:32,108
Linda always gets so proud when she
sees me sitting in here with it.

695
01:01:33,108 --> 01:01:36,942
But you've put my money in it,
haven't you?

696
01:01:39,317 --> 01:01:41,858
To make it look like it's yours.

697
01:01:50,692 --> 01:01:55,108
But it's my money, Bill.
I'm gonna have to take it.

698
01:01:55,233 --> 01:01:57,858
You can have it back.

699
01:02:00,317 --> 01:02:04,233
Y- You can...
you can have it back in a month.

700
01:02:08,942 --> 01:02:10,983
But I can't do that, Bill.

701
01:02:11,025 --> 01:02:12,525
Selma...

702
01:02:12,650 --> 01:02:18,067
I- I've decided to...
to pay the doctor this afternoon.

703
01:02:19,608 --> 01:02:23,358
I can't save up more money.
That's over now.

704
01:02:29,400 --> 01:02:32,358
Gene doesn't even turn thirteen
until after Christmas.

705
01:02:32,442 --> 01:02:40,025
There was $2,026
and ten cents in the tin.

706
01:02:41,817 --> 01:02:45,150
I can't count it now,
but I trust you.

707
01:02:46,483 --> 01:02:50,942
